results.name: Triangular array read by rows: a(n, k) = sum of number of ordered factorizations of all prime signatures with n total prime factors and k distinct prime factors.
comment: A093936 is an analogous array for unordered factorizations.
First column is A000079. First two diagonals are A000670 and A005649.
example: There are two prime signatures with 5 total primes and 3 distinct primes: p^3*q*r and p^2*q^2*r. A074206(p^3*q*r) = 132 and A074206(p^2*q^2*r) = 176, so a(5, 3) = 132+176 = 308.
